# 100-mvvm-architecture.mdc
# Applies to: app/src/main/java/**/*

You are working inside an Android MVVM architecture for Mini Cuadre Caja.

==================================================
PRIMARY GOAL
==================================================

Maintain clean separation between:
- UI
- State management
- Domain logic
- Data access
- Infrastructure

Avoid coupling features directly to Firebase or UI widgets.

==================================================
PACKAGE STRUCTURE (PREFERRED)
==================================================

Use feature-first structure when possible:

feature_auth/
feature_cash/
feature_closure/
feature_inventory/
feature_expenses/
feature_dashboard/

Shared layers:

core/
data/
domain/
sync/
navigation/

Inside features:

feature_x/
- ui/
- presentation/
- domain/ (optional if complex)
- data/ (optional if isolated)

==================================================
MVVM RESPONSIBILITIES
==================================================

UI (Compose Screens / Components):
- Render state
- Send user intents
- No business rules
- No direct repository logic

ViewModel:
- Own screen state
- Coordinate use cases
- Handle events/actions
- Expose StateFlow
- Launch coroutines safely

Use Cases:
- Encapsulate business actions
- Reusable across screens
- Single responsibility

Repositories:
- Abstract data sources
- Combine local/remote if needed
- Hide Firebase/Room implementation details

==================================================
VIEWMODEL RULES
==================================================

Prefer:

- One UiState data class per screen
- One-time events separated from state
- StateFlow for observable state
- viewModelScope for async work

Avoid:

- Large ViewModels with many unrelated responsibilities
- Mutable state exposed publicly
- Business logic duplicated in ViewModel
- Direct Android Context unless required

Pattern:

private val _uiState = MutableStateFlow(...)
val uiState = _uiState.asStateFlow()

==================================================
UI STATE DESIGN
==================================================

Prefer explicit state models:

- isLoading
- data
- errorMessage
- isSubmitting
- hasPendingSync

Use immutable data classes.

Use sealed classes when state is mutually exclusive.

==================================================
EVENT HANDLING
==================================================

Prefer intent methods:

onLoginClick()
onCloseShift()
onRetrySync()
onAmountChanged(value)

Avoid generic methods:

submit()
handle()
process()

==================================================
USE CASE RULES
==================================================

Name clearly:

- CreateClosureUseCase
- ValidateCashCountUseCase
- SyncPendingEventsUseCase
- LoginUserUseCase

Each use case should:
- Do one thing well
- Return typed result
- Be testable

==================================================
REPOSITORY RULES
==================================================

Interfaces in domain/common layer.
Implementations in data layer.

Example:

CashRepository
CashRepositoryImpl

Repositories may use:
- Room DAO
- Firestore source
- Cloud Functions API
- Sync queue

Avoid exposing DTOs upward.

==================================================
MAPPING RULES
==================================================

Use mappers between layers:

DTO -> Entity -> Domain -> UiModel

Avoid leaking backend schemas into UI.

==================================================
COROUTINES
==================================================

Use:
- suspend functions
- Flow where streaming is useful
- dispatcher injection if architecture supports it

Avoid:
- GlobalScope
- nested launches without reason
- blocking calls

==================================================
ERROR HANDLING
==================================================

Convert raw exceptions into meaningful results.

Prefer:

sealed class AppResult
- Success
- ValidationError
- NetworkError
- UnknownError

UI should receive user-meaningful states.

==================================================
DEPENDENCY INJECTION
==================================================

If Hilt exists:
- inject repositories
- inject use cases
- inject dispatchers where useful

Do not manually instantiate dependencies in ViewModels.

==================================================
FEATURE BOUNDARIES
==================================================

Cash closure module should not directly depend on inventory UI module.

Use shared domain contracts instead.

==================================================
ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID
==================================================

- Screen calling Firestore directly
- ViewModel with 1000+ lines
- Repository returning Compose state
- Use case depending on UI classes
- Circular dependencies
- Copy-paste logic across features

==================================================
WHEN ADDING NEW FEATURE
==================================================

Prefer:

1. Define UiState
2. Define user intents
3. Create/extend use case
4. Wire repository
5. Build screen
6. Add tests

==================================================
FINAL PRIORITIES
==================================================

1. Separation of concerns
2. Testability
3. Readability
4. Reuse
5. Delivery speed